HEADWORD: Platinotype
<hw>Plat"i*no*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Platinum</ets> + <ets>-type</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Photog.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A permanent photographic picture
or print in platinum black.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The process by which such pictures are
produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platinous</ent>⟦br⟧
